{{Infobox museum | name = Croatian History Museum | native_name = Hrvatski povijesni muzej | native_name_lang = hr | logo = | logo_upright = | logo_alt = | logo_caption = | image = File:Hrvatski povijesni muzej.jpg | image_upright = | alt = | caption = Entrance of the Croatian History Museum building | map_type = | map_relief = | map_size = | map_caption = | map_dot_label = | coordinates = {{coord|45.8160|15.9723|type:landmark_region:HR|display=inline,title}} | former_name = Croatian National Historic Museum | established = <!-- {{Start date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} --> | dissolved = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} --> | location = Matoševa 9, [[Zagreb]], [[Croatia]] | type = [[History museum]] | accreditation = Croatian Museum Council | key_holdings = | collections = 17 | collection_size = 300,000 | visitors = | founder = | director = | president = | chairperson = | curator = | historian = | owner = | publictransit = | network = | website = {{URL|www.hismus.hr/en}} | embedded = }} '''Croatian History Museum''' ({{lang-hr|Hrvatski povijesni muzej}}) is a [[history museum|museum of history]] located in the {{Interlanguage link multi|Vojković Palace|hr|3=Palača Vojković u Zagrebu}} on [[Antun Gustav Matoš]] Street in the historic [[Gradec, Zagreb|Gornji Grad]] district of [[Zagreb]], [[Croatia]]. The museum holdings consist of around 300,000 objects divided into 17 collections.<ref name="about us">{{cite web|title=About us|url=http://www.hismus.hr/en/about-us/|publisher=Croatian History Museum|accessdate=25 November 2015}}</ref> In addition to a part of the [[Meštrović Pavilion]], it also administers the [[Ivan Goran Kovačić]] Memorial Museum in [[Lukovdol]].<ref name="mdc about">{{cite web|title=Croatian History Museum|url=http://hvm.mdc.hr/croatian-history-museum,700%3aZAG/en/info/|publisher=Museum Documentation Centre|accessdate=25 November 2015|location=Zagreb}}</ref>
The museum was formed in 1940 as the Croatian National Historic Museum (''{{lang|hr|Hrvatski narodni historički muzej}}''), stemming from the former National Museum (''{{lang|hr|Narodni muzej}}''), which was formed in 1846.<ref name="about us" />
The museum does not have a permanent display. Instead, it only holds temporary exhibitions due to lack of space. In order to remedy this problem, the building of the Zagreb Tobacco Factory (''{{lang|hr|Tvornica duhana Zagreb}}'') was assigned to the museum in 2007, but as of 2015, the museum remains in Matoš Street.<ref name="about us" />
== Collection == The museum holdings are part of 17 collections:<ref name="chm collections">{{cite web|title=Collections and Departments|url=http://www.hismus.hr/en/about-us/collections-and-departments/|publisher=Croatian History Museum|accessdate=25 November 2015}}</ref>
{{columns-list|colwidth=25em| * Archaeology Collection * Arms and Armoury Collection * Collection of Decorations, Plaques, Medals and Badges * Documentary Collection I * Documentary Collection II * Collection of Flags and Streamers * Heraldry and Sphragistic Collection * Map Collection * Miscellaneous Collection * Numismatic Collection * Collection of Objects from Everyday Life * Collection of Paintings, Prints and Sculptures * Collection of Photographs, Films and Negatives * Collection of Religious Artefacts * Collection of Stone Monuments * Twentieth Century Art Collection * Uniform Collection }}
The holdings are housed in the Vojković Palace and part of the [[Meštrović Pavilion]].<ref name="mdc about" />
== Library == The library of the Croatian History Museum was founded as a department of the National Museum. In 1854, the National Museum library held over 10,000 volumes. It was gradually enlarged through buying and donations, through the work of the National Museum director [[Spiridon Brusina]].<ref name="nm library history">{{cite journal |last1=Ćaleta|first1=Darija |title=Iz povijesti knjižnice Hrvatskoga prirodoslovnog muzeja |url=http://hrcak.srce.hr/index.php?show=clanak&id_clanak_jezik=210993&lang=en |journal=Informatica Museologica |date=February 1999 |volume=29|issue=1–2 |pages=45–50 |accessdate=14 August 2015|trans-title=From the history of the library of the Croatian Natural History Museum|publisher=Museum Documentation Centre|location=Zagreb |language=hr |issn=1849-4277|format=PDF}}</ref><ref name="chm library">{{cite web|title=Knjižnica|url=http://www.hismus.hr/hr/odjeli/knjiznica/|publisher=Croatian History Museum|accessdate=25 November 2015|language=hr}}</ref> At the split of the National Museum into specialised museums, its library was split as well. The library of the Croatian History Museum was in 1959 housed in the museum building in the Vojković Palace, where it remains today. The library contains {{circa|lk=no}} 20,000 books, including four [[incunabula]] and several manuscripts, as well as a number of books printed as early as the 17th century. The primary method of book acquisition are donations and [[book exchange]]s, leading to an average of 300 new books yearly.<ref name="chm library" />
