'''Ooni Orarigba''' was the 44th [[Ooni of Ife]], a paramount traditional ruler of [[Ile Ife]], the ancestral home of the [[Yoruba people|Yorubas]]. He succeeded Ooni [[Ooni Degbinsokun]] and was succeeded by Ooni [[Derin Ologbenla]].<Ref>{{cite book |last=Dayo|first= Ologundudu|date=2008 |title=The cradle of Yoruba culture|url=https://books.google.com/?id=Vn8uAQAAIAAJ&q=Ooni+Ojigidiri&dq=Ooni+Ojigidiri|location= Nigeria|publisher=Centre for spoken words |page=206 |isbn=0615220630 |access-date=July 30, 2015}}</ref>

