'''Paterius''' (died 606) was a [[bishop of Brescia]]. He is known as a compiler, in particular of works of [[Pope Gregory I]], for whom he worked as a notary.

His sole surviving work is the ''Liber testimoniorum veteris testamenti'',<ref>Schøyen 2008</ref> an anthology of Gregory's biblical [[exegesis]], arranged in the order of the biblical passages discussed. The work survives in over 120 complete or partial [[manuscript]]s.<ref>Martello 2012, p. 435</ref>

